Operational shell scripts for the monorepo. These are the only entry points humans and CI use — they must work from any current directory.

# lang Bash {#bash_lang}

Bash via `#!/usr/bin/env bash`, with `set -euo pipefail` as the first statement after the shebang. POSIX-friendly otherwise; no bashisms beyond arrays and `[[ ]]`. Scripts are `chmod +x` and shellcheck-clean.

# good Script Discipline {#bash_patterns}

- Resolve the repository root once — `ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")/.." && pwd)"` — and build every path from `$ROOT`; never depend on the caller's working directory.
- Every variable expansion is double-quoted.
- Scripts log through a local `log <LEVEL> <message>` function that emits the shared logging format (service name: `scripts`) to stderr.

# bad Shell Hazards {#bash_hazards}

- No `curl | sh`, no network access at all — everything needed is in the repo.
- No `rm -rf` on any path containing a variable.
- No silencing failures with `|| true`.
